342 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: PULLED UP BY A THREAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trisha Yearwood's "Song Remembers When" is a big seller (No. 8) on The Times' 
Southern California album chart partly because of another album, "Common 
Thread: Songs of the Eagles." Exposure on this country-chart topper (she sings 
"New Kid in Town") has beefed up her fan base. George Strait is doing something 
Garth Brooks used to do, with several albums in the country Top 10. Strait's 
"Easy Come Easy Go" is No. 6 and his "Pure Country" is No. 10. Celine Dion's 
"Power of Love" is powering its way up the pop singles chart, debuting at No. 
8. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,42,11 Title, Artist (National Rank) Last Week 1 
Doggystyle, Snoop Doggy Dogg (4) 1 2 Music Box, Mariah Carey (1) 3 3 Vs., Pearl 
Jam (2) 2 4 Lethal Injection, Ice Cube (19) 4 5 Toni Braxton, Toni Braxton (12) 
