<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO -- The Year of the Dog, Lunar Calendar Year 4692, officially 
begins Feb. 10, and festivities are scheduled Feb. 5-27. A highlight will be 
the San Francisco Chronicle Chinese New Year Parade, 5:30 p.m. Feb. 26.A 
community fair will be in Chinatown Feb. 26-27. For a complete schedule, call 
(415) 391-9680, or send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: San Francisco 
Chronicle Chinese New Year Festival and Parade, Golden Gateway Station, P.O. 
Box 2653, San Francisco 94126. 
</P>
<P>
 HOLTVILLE -- Sing the praises of the popular orange root at the Holtville 
Carrot Festival, Feb. 9-13. This year's event features a parade at 10 a.m. Feb. 
12 on 5th Street, and a festival in Holtville City Park, Feb. 12-13. Other 
events: A carnival and a rib cook-off. (619) 356-2923. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- Celebrate Fat Tuesday, New Orleans-style, at the 16th 
annual Mardi Gras Festival, Feb. 12. A free street fair is set for 10 a.m.-5 
p.m. on Garden Street, a parade is at 7:15 p.m. along Higuera Street, and the 
Masked Ball and Buffet Banquet is at 8 p.m. at the Veterans Memorial Hall, 801 
Grand Ave. $25. (805) 541-2183. 
</P>
<P>
 LAGUNA BEACH -- Take your Valentine to the 30th annual Winterfest, Feb. 12-14 
at the Festival of the Arts grounds, 650 Laguna Canyon Road. 11 a.m.-dusk 
daily. About 150 artisans expected. $3, general; $2, seniors; $1, kids 12 and 
under. (714) 494-1018, Ext. 5. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</TEXT>
