<HEADLINE>
<P>
MY BEST SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frosene Papahronis of Fullerton spent three years working and traveling 
throughout the Far East.She took at least 500 pictures, but this portrait of a 
mother and child, which she snapped near Mae Sai, in northern Thailand, is one 
of her favorites. "Taking pictures of people is the best," she says. "I liked 
this one so much that I blew it up to put on the wall. It captures the ornate 
beauty of the traditional dress of the Akha people." 
</P>
</TEXT>
