<P>
LESLIE HITS MILESTONE AS USC WINS, 101-70 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lisa Leslie scored 31 points to surpass the 2,000-point mark, and No. 9-ranked 
USC defeated Washington State, 101-70, Saturday night at the Lyon Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Leslie has 2,001 points, fourth-highest in USC history and second in Pacific 
10 Conference women's basketball history. She had 17 rebounds, three assists, 
three blocks and four steals.  
</P>
<P>
 USC (11-1, 4-0) scored 25 consecutive points in opening a 25-5 lead. Jenni 
Ruff led the Cougars (6-7, 1-3) with 19 points and seven rebounds. 
</P>
