<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CANYONS GETS LESSON FROM MOORPARK, 86-73 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Danny Alexander scored 25 points and Paul Foster had 23 and 12 rebounds to 
lead the Moorpark College men's basketball team to an 86-73 victory over 
Canyons in a Western State Conference game Saturday night at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaime Jaquez added 12 points and 10 rebounds and Sean Martin had 12 points and 
14 assists for Moorpark (18-5, 4-1 in WSC play). 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Eason had 23 points and 14 rebounds for Canyons (6-14). 
</P>
<P>
 In other men's basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 101, Redlands 93 -- Damon Ridley scored 30 points at Redlands as 
the Kingsmen won their 13th game without a defeat. Cal Lutheran, 2-0 in SCIAC 
play, has scored more than 100 points in each of its league victories. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 90, Christian Heritage 70 -- Leo Goravakas (15 points) and Emeka 
Okenwa (14) led seven Mustangs (17-3) in double figures in a nonconference game 
in Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 Cuesta 71, Valley 70 -- Conlon Bryant hit a three-pointer with 14 seconds left 
to give the Cougars a 71-67 lead and seal a WSC victory in San Luis Obispo. 
Darius Moses had 16 points and 11 rebounds the Monarchs (8-12, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 96, Barstow 73 -- Orville Turner had 26 points and six 
assists, Gary Boyce scored 18 points and Marcus Cross added 16 points and nine 
rebounds for Antelope Valley (11-9, 3-2) in a Foothill Conference game. MEN'S 
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara Invitational -- Cal State Northridge defeated UCSB, 15-12, 
16-14, to finish ninth in the tournament at Goleta. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier, the Matadors lost to UCLA, 15-8, 10-15, 16-14, and to Pacific, 15-9, 
15-13, in Pool II play. WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Sacramento 84, Northridge 64 -- Kristy Ryan had 38 points and 19 
rebounds for the Hornets (9-6) in a nonconference victory in Sacramento. 
Shannon Crouse scored 19 for CSUN (2-14). 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 71, Santa Barbara 68 -- Keri Peterson's layup tied the score with 
five seconds left in regulation and Cindy Thai's two free throws with 45 
seconds left in overtime clinched a WSC victory for the Vaqueros (8-8, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 69, Moorpark 57 -- Jeanette Oriza had 16 points for the Raiders, who 
took their first WSC setback in the game at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 65, Cuesta 54 -- Vonya Dangerfield scored 15 points to lead the 
Monarchs (8-14, 3-3) in a WSC game at Cuesta. Valley point guard Maggie Hause 
scored 11 points and had six steals. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce 72, Oxnard 57 -- Angela Rich scored 24 points to lead the Brahmas 
(4-13, 2-3) to a WSC victory at Oxnard. 
</P>
