<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FIELD HOCKEY; NEWPORT HARBOR FALLS IN TOURNAMENT FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Verne Bonita captured the championship of the Orange County Invitational 
field hockey tournament for the second consecutive year, defeating Newport 
Harbor, 2-0, on Saturday at Fountain Valley High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Tracy Huigens scored both goals for Bonita and was named tournament MVP.Sara 
Raymond had five saves for the Sailors. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor (4-2-2) reached the finals by defeating Glendora, 1-0, in the 
semifinals. Mara Collaizzi scored the game-winner for the Sailors and was named 
to the all-tournament team, along with teammates Buffy Carpenter and Danielle 
Dwyer. Newport Harbor is second in the Sunset League behind Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers (6-2), leaders in the Sunset League, finished third in the 
tournament with a 1-0 victory over Glendora. Jennifer Craig, named to the 
all-tournament team, scored for Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 Also named to the all-tournament team were Nicole Nehrig (Edison), Erica 
Crandall (Fountain Valley), Catherine Raspet (Fountain Valley), Michelle Carr 
(Fountain Valley), Sonya Deffner (Huntington Beach), Jayne Davis (Marina), 
Sarah Ewing (Marina) and Alicia Alvarado (Santiago). 
</P>
</TEXT>
