<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; COTTON, MCKNIGHT, SIMON LEAD MATER DEI PAST SAVANNA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Schea Cotton had 28 points and 15 rebounds to lead No. 1 Mater Dei 
over Savanna, 84-51, in nonleague action at UC Irvine's Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Miles Simon, who broke a school record Friday night with 15 assists, had 12 
Saturday along with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Clay McKnight hit four three-pointers for the Monarchs to finish with 16 
points and Shaun Jackson added 13 points and 10 rebounds. Mater Dei remains 
undefeated at 19-0 and 3-0 in the South Coast League. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos Valley Christian 58, Brethren Christian 46 -- Steve DeGraaf scored a 
game-high 22 points for Valley Christian (5-11, 2-3). Lance Williams added 15. 
Richard Mendoza led Brethren Christian with 13 points. Brethren Christian is 
10-6 and 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 63, Orange Lutheran 60 -- With one second remaining, Ryan 
Elliot made two free throws to give Calvary Chapel (9-9, 3-1) the victory. 
Isaac Lesau scored with 20 seconds remaining to put Calvary Chapel ahead, 
61-59. Orange Lutheran had a chance to regain the lead when Tom Howard was 
fouled behind the three-point line, but he converted only one of three free 
throws. Kevin Falconer led both teams with 15 points for Calvary Chapel. Jason 
Chedotte added 14. Orange Lutheran is 1-13, 0-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 71, Ontario Christian 67 -- Kwadwo Boachie had 19 points, 
eight assists and six steals and Tyler Ream added 19 points and 10 rebounds for 
Whittier Christian (14-2, 5-0). Harlan Miersma had 22 points for Ontario 
Christian. 
</P>
