<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lawsuit Settled: Thanh Son Tofu, a food processing company in Westminster, has 
settled a consumer protection lawsuit brought by the Orange County district 
attorney.The lawsuit alleged that the company, owned by Xuan Van Dang and Di 
Ta, had sold tofu and soybean products that were processed in unsanitary 
conditions. 
</P>
<P>
 Without admitting any wrongdoing, the defendants agreed to pay $8,961 in civil 
penalties and adopt a comprehensive plan to protect public health. That plan 
includes training for employees who handle foods, improved sanitation practices 
and a pledge to keep the company's food-processing area free of rodents. 
</P>
