<P>
FRENCH SUSPECT ADMITS KILLING 5 ELDERLY WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A jobless, 22-year-old man has confessed to the killings of five elderly 
women, including the sister of the national railroad company's president, 
police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Claude Lastennet was arrested Wednesday in a suburb west of Paris and told 
investigators he had "killed for the sake of killing," police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims ranged in age from 73 to 92. 
</P>
