<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANTI-FASCISTS, SKINHEADS CLASH IN EAST LONDON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Right-wing extremists and anti-fascist youths clashed Saturday at an east 
London underground train station, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said 10 people were arrested during battles at East Ham station 
believed to be between supporters of the Anti-Nazi League and right-wing 
skinheads. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokeswoman said police also held about 100 left-wing youths at Bow Road, 
another underground station in east London, to prevent them from boarding 
trains thought to be carrying right-wingers. They would be allowed to disperse 
later. 
</P>
