<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; FBI SEEKS SUSPECT IN 5 BANK ROBBERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The FBI is looking for a man suspected of robbing five banks in Ventura County 
in the last six months, as well as two other banks during that same period in 
Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
 The FBI released a photo of the man taken by closed-circuit cameras during a 
robbery Jan. 11 at the Great Western Bank in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect appears to be in his 40s, about 6 feet, 1 inch tall and weighing 
195 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 In each of the seven robberies, the man has handed a teller a note asking for 
money and warning that he has a weapon, the FBI said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other robberies in Ventura County were at the Great Western Bank in Port 
Hueneme on Dec. 18; Bank of America in Camarillo on Aug. 6; Bank of A. Levy in 
Thousand Oaks on Aug. 3, and at the First State Bank of the Oaks in Thousand 
Oaks on July 9. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Crime Stoppers has offered up to $1,000 for any information 
leading to the arrest of the suspect, an east county Sheriff's Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with any information is asked to call the FBI at 642-3995 or Crime 
Stoppers at 987-TALK. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
