<HEADLINE>
<P>
50,000 HOMELESS IN WEST JAVA FLOODS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Floods inundated wide areas around the city of Bandung in West Java, forcing 
tens of thousands of people to flee their homes, the official news agency 
Antara said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Antara said four villages were swamped when heavy rains caused the Citarum 
River to overflow. The flood waters rose higher than 8 feet, villagers told 
Antara. 
</P>
<P>
 Waters flooded rice fields and about 6,000 houses, offices, schools and other 
public buildings. More than 50,000 people have been left homeless in Bandung 
and outlying districts, the news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
