<P>
RIVAL AFGHAN FIGHTING SPREADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fighting among rival Afghan factions seeking power in Kabul spread to three 
northern provinces Saturday as the struggle entered its third week, Afghan 
sources in Pakistan said. 
</P>
<P>
 Each side claimed victories in the Afghan capital itself, where jets from 
opposing sides bombed enemy positions during ground fighting, the sources said. 
</P>
<P>
 Forces loyal to President Burhanuddin Rabbani and his opponents were also 
engaged in new fighting in the northern provinces of Samangan, Jozjan and 
Balkh, they added. 
</P>
