<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL WHO APPARENTLY CUT SWASTIKA IN OWN CHEEK SURRENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A wheelchair-bound schoolgirl who disappeared after apparently making up a 
story about skinheads carving a swastika on her cheek has surrendered to 
authorities, German police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman in Halle said the 17-year-old vanished Thursday after police 
launched a nationwide search for three skinheads she claimed had attacked her 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Doctors have told investigators they believe the Nazi-emblem cut on her face 
was self-inflicted. 
</P>
<P>
 "We now know where the girl is," the spokesman said. "She is with her parents 
at a relative's house at a location far away from Halle. The relatives phoned 
us this morning. The girl is expected to be back in Halle tomorrow." 
</P>
<P>
 Saxony-Anhalt state prosecutor Juergen Hossfeld said investigators had 
concluded the girl made up the story about the attack that had shocked a nation 
struggling to come to terms with a rise in right-wing violence. 
</P>
<P>
 Hossfeld said the girl may have fled because she feared the legal consequences 
of lying to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Police officials in Halle on Saturday declined to say what, if any, charges 
may be filed against the girl. 
</P>
<P>
 Hossfeld said investigators had searched intensively for the alleged culprits 
but there had been no leads. 
</P>
<P>
 He said doubts arose early in the search because no suspects and no witnesses 
turned up despite a hunt by more than 100 police. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl's cuts were judged to be too uniformly deep to have been the work of 
an assailant and indicated the wound was self-inflicted, according to doctors 
working with the investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
