<TEXT>
<P>
 A 32-year-old mother drowned Saturday in Jackson Lake while trying to rescue 
her son who had fallen through the ice, Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10-year-old boy, whose name was not released, was playing on the edge of 
the ice-covered lake with his mother about 1 p.m. when he fell through the ice, 
said Sgt. Gil Arce of the Antelope Valley Sheriff's Station. 
</P>
<P>
 "The mother went to help along with two other family members, and they also 
fell through," Arce said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bystanders were able to use a makeshift rope to rescue everyone but the 
mother, whose body was retrieved by a sheriff's dive team, Arce said. The boy 
was taken to San Bernardino Hospital, where he was being treated for mild 
hypothermia, Arce said. 
