<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL; SECOND EFFORT LIFTS LACC OVER TRADE TECH, 69-58 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles City College is playing the best basketball among local community 
colleges. But before the third-ranked team in the state could stake its claim 
to No. 1 in the area, it had to beat last year's best, Trade Tech. 
</P>
<P>
 After trailing 39-32 at halftime, LACC scored the first nine points of the 
second half en route to a 69-58 win Friday night in a Southern California 
Athletic Conference game at Trade Tech. 
</P>
<P>
 "We picked up the intensity in the second half because we knew whoever wanted 
to win the most would," said LACC guard Markee Brown, who scored a game-high 19 
points. "Tonight, I had to step up my game." 
</P>
<P>
 Forward Terry Green, who led the Beavers with 18 points, shouldered much of 
the offensive burden for Trade Tech (12-11, 0-1 in conference) in the second 
half. Green hit back-to-back three pointers to bring Trade Tech to within two, 
45-43, early in the second half. Green also had five rebounds and two steals 
and scored 12 points in the first half to help give Trade Tech an early 18-14 
advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 After Trade Tech's second-half scoring run, Brown capped a 14-7 LACC run with 
a short baseline jumper to increase the Cubs' lead to 59-50. 
</P>
<P>
 Sai Tuialii scored 18 points, 14 in the second half, for LACC (19-3, 1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. CITY COLLEGE -- Muhammad 4, Bean 2, Higgins 9, Brown 19, Tuialii 18, 
Moore 2, Dorsey 8, Thomas 2, Cotwright 5. 
</P>
<P>
 TRADE TECH -- Lew 10, Dawson 3, Crutchfield 9, Green 18, Wesby 5, Yoakum 2, 
Martin 4, Wade 2, McDowell 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Records: LACC 19-3, 1-0 in conference; Trade Tech 12-11, 0-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
