<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; BANNING OUTLASTS WASHINGTON IN THREE OTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN WATERS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Washington High's Surviving Seven nearly pulled off the biggest upset of the 
year before losing to Banning, 70-65, in triple overtime Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The seven players, who began the season as reserves, moved into starting roles 
when six Generals, including four starters, were suspended for three games for 
an unspecified incident. The other General starter was out sick with the flu. 
</P>
<P>
 The Surviving Seven were down to five -- two players fouled out by the first 
overtime -- when Jason Pickett single-handedly saved the Pilots from possible 
embarrassment. 
</P>
<P>
 Pickett scored 44 points for Washington, including the final two points in the 
fourth quarter and the first two overtimes. 
</P>
<P>
 With no time remaining in the second overtime, Pickett made an off-balance 
jump shot to tie the score at 61. Brian Perkins then scored six points in the 
third overtime for the Pilots. 
</P>
