<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; BANNING OUTLASTS WASHINGTON IN THREE OTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Washington High's Surviving Seven nearly pulled off the biggest upset of the 
year before losing to Banning, 70-65, in triple overtime Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The seven players, who began the season as reserves, moved into starting roles 
when six Generals, including four starters, were suspended for three games for 
an unspecified incident. The other General starter was out sick with the flu. 
</P>
<P>
 The Surviving Seven were down to five -- two players fouled out by the first 
overtime -- when Jason Pickett single-handedly saved the Pilots from possible 
embarrassment. 
</P>
<P>
 Pickett scored 44 points for Washington, including the final two points in the 
fourth quarter and the first two overtimes. 
</P>
<P>
 With no time remaining in the second overtime, Pickett made an off-balance 
jump shot to tie the score at 61. Brian Perkins then scored six points in the 
third overtime for the Pilots. 
</P>
<P>
 BANNING -- Pickett 44, Perkins 12, Jett 4, Jackson 1, McCrimmon 4, Brown 3, 
Patterson 2. 
</P>
<P>
 WASHINGTON -- Fitzgerald 6, Williams 18, Lewis 13, Moore 4, Sparks 14, Jelks 
6, Isam 4. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorsey 84, Gardena 61 -- Sherwyn Morgan had 20 points, including three 
three-point baskets, to pace the Dons in a Southern Pacific Conference game 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 DORSEY -- Munday 10, Morgan 20, Thymes 2, Blackmon 16, McCluster 4, Colbert 5, 
McKnight 5, O'Nea 9, Johnson 8, Frazier 3, Shumate 2. 
</P>
<P>
 GARDENA -- Polk 2, Dyson 6, Hawkins 6, Brigham 6, Mitchell 13, Carter 10, 
House 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan 81, South Gate 71 -- Clem Breedlove scored 34 points as Jordan won a 
Southeastern Conference game Friday at home. 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH GATE -- Bellar 2, Miranda 8, Rios 4, Herrera 12, Dacal 2, Gallardo 13, 
Balanos 5, Plascencia 3, Corona 22. 
</P>
<P>
 JORDAN -- Barrett 16, Cabada 2, Breedlove 34, Goss 24, Medrano 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw 145, Narbonne 63 -- Forward Tremaine Fowlkes scored a game-high 32 
points and Kris Johnson added 27 in a Southern Pacific game Friday at Crenshaw. 
</P>
<P>
 NARBONNE -- Augustus 5, Brown 4, Burris 2, Heads 2, Hernandez 10, Taylor 2, 
Terry 25, Thimes 11, Watkins 2. 
</P>
<P>
