</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire officials are investigating a blaze at the Family Farm Market that caused 
more than $1 million worth of damage and injured three people. 
</P>
<P>
 "The building was heavily damaged," said Jim Wells, a spokesman for the Los 
Angeles Fire Department. "There was heavy smoke by the time firefighters 
arrived." 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze at 4322 S. Central Ave. began shortly before 9:42 p.m. Jan. 9 at the 
one-story building. 
</P>
<P>
 Two firefighters suffered minor injuries and one woman was treated at the 
scene for minor respiratory problems, said Jim Wells, a spokesman for the Los 
Angeles Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Wells said the fire was being investigated as an independent incident and 
declined to say where the fire began. SANDRA HERNANDEZ 
