<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; POLITICS: NOVEMBER VOTE ON CIVIC CENTER? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Opponents of the Santa Monica Civic Center redevelopment plan don't know yet 
whether their referendum has qualified for the ballot, but they do know which 
ballot they want it on: November's. 
</P>
<P>
 In separate letters to Mayor Judy Abdo state Sen. Tom Hayden (D-Santa Monica) 
and the opponents' group, Citizens for a Better Civic Center, urged delaying a 
vote until November to save money.They claim it will be $80,000 cheaper than a 
special election and $50,000 cheaper than adding the referendum to the June 
ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 But Abdo said her preference is to deal with the matter sooner rather than 
later. Art: Getty Names Curator of Paintings 
</P>
<P>
 The J. Paul Getty Museum in Malibu has appointed David A. Jaffe as curator of 
paintings. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaffe, 40, formerly curator of European art at the Australian National Gallery 
in Canberra, was named to the Getty position last week. He is a well-known 
scholar of Baroque art, particularly the work of Peter Paul Rubens. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaffe was educated at the University of Melbourne and at the Courtauld 
Institute of Art at the University of London, where in 1978 he received a 
master's degree in art history. 
</P>
<P>
 He taught at the University of Queensland in Australia from 1982 to 1990 
before joining the Australian National Gallery as curator of 19th-Century 
European art. Education: Meeting on Financial Aid 
</P>
<P>
 A financial aid workshop for college-bound high school seniors and their 
parents is scheduled for Jan. 25 at the Santa Monica High School cafeteria at 7 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 A Santa Monica College student aid counselor will provide information on 
deadlines and the types of financial aid available, and will help fill out 
forms. 
</P>
<P>
 Spanish translators also will be available. Santa Monica High School is at 601 
Pico Blvd. Information: (310) 395-3204. 
</P>
